./sdp/logs/Lead_Tery phrase declares an intent tag (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate). Parameters are chosen so the intent is perceptible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. **Restraint as material.** Silence is scheduled, not residual. Density and silence budgets are maintained per voice and per section.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. **Machine identity preserved.** Grid-locked elements (ostinati, sequencers, polyrhythmic machines), superhuman precision, and alien timbres are deliberately *not* humanized. CypherClaw is a robot musician that has learned which things humans shape — not a robot pretending to be a violinist.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The goal is not realism. It is **legibility**: a listener should feel that CypherClaw *intended* each phrase — to build, to withhold, to answer the room.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Scope and non-goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**In scope:** a new rendering stage between composition and synthesis; an Event/PerformanceIntent/SectionEnvelope data model with rule-stack provenance; a 12-rule render stack (R1–R12); a seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds; a replay harness; a rule-ablation debugger; a metrics-CI gate with anti-pattern detection; a performance-worm diagnostic; a bounded sensor-to-intent aggregation matrix.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Out of scope / non-goals:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Photorealistic human-performance imitation. CypherClaw is a robot musician, not a violinist simulator.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- General-purpose MIDI humanizer — this is not a plugin.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Sensor-driven note generation. Sensors modulate expression, never replace composition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Machine-learning performance models in this phase. Rule-based KTH-style is interpretable, debuggable, and gateable with fixed metrics. Learned models can be added after the metric gate is stable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Replacement of existing composition, production-course, or synthesis work. This layer sits *above* synthesis and *below* composition — it renders what the composer emits.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## The four phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCH-001..CCH-010).** Data model, seeded-RNG plumbing, replay harness, rule-ablation debugger. At end of phase, existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline with no rules active — just plumbing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 2 — Core rule stack (CCH-011..CCH-021).** R1 Metric Accent, R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH parabolic), R3 Agogic Accent, R4 Duration Contrast, R5 Final Ritardando (Friberg–Sundberg square-root), R6 Punctuation+Breath, R7 Articulation Shaping, R8 Microtiming Polish (below JND). Role-filter gating so grid-locked voices skip the stack. Phrase-feature extraction via partitura. End-of-phase: single-voice melodic passages sound shaped, not flat; metric gate shows structured deviations vs. flat-line baseline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 3 — Memory, silence, ensemble (CCH-022..CCH-029).** R9 Motif memory with LRU + variation menu + return-home decay. R10 Silence budgets with wind-voice lung-capacity caps. R11 Call-response gating. Section-level envelope compositing. Tempo-dependent swing (Friberg/Sundström). Arc-shape variety. Restraint as global dampener. End-of-phase: 5-minute generative pieces no longer feel looped; repetition-variance metrics pass thresholds.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 4 — Sensor aggregation + narrative coupling (CCH-030..CCH-033).** R12 Sensor-to-intent matrix (smoothed IIR, hysteresis, aggregate intentions — never one-to-one). Bounded reactive delta track. Narrative engine → SectionEnvelope coupling. End-of-phase: installation responds legibly to audience presence without gimmicky mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Metrics-CI Gate + Diagnostics (CCH-034..CCH-040).** Metric battery, anti-pattern detection, performance-worm logger, CI integration, audio-rendered cross-check, provenance in exported audio metadata, listener-review workflow. Runs in parallel with rule-stack build-out; most checks land alongside the rule they validate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Depends on\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md` — the currently-executing PRD covering production profiles, harmonic library, SenseWeave mappings, genre strategies, phase transitions. Rules R1–R8 read phase profiles and harmonic-function metadata from that layer.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` — the score-tree composer this layer renders from.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` — reference for existing musicianship vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime, master bus, self-listener, Theramini modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Key files and modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/` package:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/events.py` — Event, PerformanceIntent, SectionEnvelope, IntentTag, Role dataclasses\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/seed.py` — per-stage sub-seed derivation, replay harness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/pass_.py` — RenderPass framework, ordered rule stack, ablation support\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/features.py` — partitura-backed phrase/harmonic feature extraction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/replay.py` — bit-identical (score, seed, delta_track) → performed_part reproduction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/worm.py` — performance-worm logger and convex-hull diagnostic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/metrics.py` — IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR, GS, pitch H1, LZ76, tempo autocorrelation, silence coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/antipatterns.py` — quantization-ghosting, dynamic-compression, motif-ossification, random-as-expression, symmetric-arc-uncanny, dead-silence detectors\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` — score-tree nodes carry PerformanceIntent / SectionEnvelope metadata\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py` — emits score-tree with new metadata; composition seed threaded through\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py` — gate checks new metadata present on all phrases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/music_tracker.py` / `music_tracker_runtime.py` — tracker scenes preserve Event metadata through compile → schedule\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py` — surface active rule stack, current phrase intent, worm snapshot\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_render_*.py` — per-rule, role-filter, replay, ablation, metric, anti-pattern tests\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+|----|-------------|----------|------|---------------------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-007 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | MUST | T1 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-008 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | MUST | T1 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-010 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | MUST | T1 | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-014 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-016 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-017 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-018 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-021 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | MUST | T1 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-023 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-024 | Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. | MUST | T1 | - voices with lung_capacity set (default 6 s for winds/voice, null for others) track continuous sounding time<br/>- exceeding cap forces a breath at next phrase boundary or earlier if density tolerates<br/>- tests verify cap enforcement and breath insertion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-026 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | MUST | T1 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-027 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | MUST | T1 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-028 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | MUST | T1 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-030 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-031 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | MUST | T1 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-033 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | MUST | T1 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-034 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, Mu\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Random-as-expression.** Gaussian jitter without structured deviation. Ljung-Box must reject white-noise null on tempo and velocity series.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Enthusiastic rule application.** Doubling every k produces caricature, not more expression. Defaults are calibrated and per-piece overrides must be justified.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Forgetting machine identity.** If a rule leaks onto grid-locked voices, the render fails the role-filter gate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **One-to-one sensor gimmickry.** No listener-reverse-engineerable sensor → parameter mapping.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Symmetric-arc uncanny.** Every phrase cannot have the same parabolic shape.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Permanent novelty / no return home.** Motif memory must bring the original back within ~8 iterations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Dead-silence failure.** A 2-minute melodic passage with no rests ≥200 ms fails — silence is a first-class voice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/requirements-register.md b/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 35ffd6a..f31011e 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,32 +1,47 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# Requirements Register — PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Requirements Register — PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Extracted:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472602+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total requirements:** 25\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Extracted:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.336519+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total requirements:** 40\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Section |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |----|-------------|----------|------|---------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-001 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-003 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-004 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-005 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-006 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-007 | Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. | SHOULD | T2 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-008 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-009 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-010 | Add dynamics, compression, sidechain, and deference policy. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-011 | Add spatial, reverb, and delay production profiles. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-012 | Complete mastering and loudness policy for installation playback. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-014 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-016 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-017 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-018 | Add phase-transition composition techniques. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-019 | Build SuperCollider recipe references without coupling tests to live audio. | SHOULD | T2 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-020 | Wire production-course choices into score trees and tracker output. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-021 | Extend the composition gate with production-course checks. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-022 | Add course-driven self-critique and revision targets. | SHOULD | T2 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-023 | Turn the production course into executable curriculum exercises. | SHOULD | T2 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-024 | Add operator diagnostics for production-course decisions. | SHOULD | T2 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-025 | Add end-to-end production-course integration tests. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ No newline at end of file\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-007 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-008 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-010 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-014 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-016 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-017 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-018 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-021 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache ofity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 15 | T-015 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-003 | T-001 | - triads, seventh chords, extended chords, altered dominants, suspended/add chords, drop voicings, close/open voicings, and rootless/guide-tone voicings are supported<br/>- voicing engine respects register limits and configured spacing<br/>- tests verify chord pitch classes, unique voicings, range safety, and smooth voice-leading choices |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 16 | T-016 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-004 | T-001 | - harmonic planner can label tonic, subdominant, dominant, secondary dominant, modal-interchange, tritone-sub, chromatic-mediant, pedal, planing, and modulation functions<br/>- score trees expose harmonic function and transition intent per section<br/>- tests verify cadence resolution, pivot/common-tone modulation continuity, and phase-appropriate tension levels |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 17 | T-017 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-005 | T-001 | - rhythm engine supports 4/4, 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8, free/rubato, swing, shuffle, dotted cells, push/pull, polyrhythm, polymeter, and metric modulation<br/>- tracker metadata carries meter, subdivision, swing ratio, groove timing, and phrase breath without breaking deterministic row scheduling<br/>- tests verify IOI ratios, swing offsets, polyrhythm cycle length, and phase-specific meter policies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 18 | T-018 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-006 | T-001 | - arrangement/compiler can choose contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, and completion relationships between lanes<br/>- dissonance and resolution rules are available as metadata checks<br/>- tests verify independent lane contours, staggered climaxes, and no accidental lane crowding |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 19 | T-019 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-008 | T-001 | - registry covers subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT processing with safe parameter ranges and arc-phase affinities<br/>- score tree or tracker scenes can request synthesis architecture by production role<br/>- tests verify each architecture has role tags, macro controls, safe ranges, and fallbacks |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 20 | T-020 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-009 | T-001 | - mix engine assigns sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, and air lanes to roles<br/>- production metadata includes HPF/LPF/EQ intent for bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, and Theramini lanes<br/>- tests verify role frequency lanes avoid primary masking and preserve bass center policy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 19 | T-019 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCH-020 | T-011 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 20 | T-020 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-021 | T-011 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 21 | T-021 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-022 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 22 | T-022 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-023 | T-011 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 23 | T-023 | Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-024 | T-011 | - voices with lung_capacity set (default 6 s for winds/voice, null for others) track continuous sounding time<br/>- exceeding cap forces a breath at next phrase boundary or earlier if density tolerates<br/>- tests verify cap enforcement and breath insertion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 24 | T-024 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-025 | T-011 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 25 | T-025 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-026 | T-011 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 26 | T-026 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-027 | T-011 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 27 | T-027 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-028 | T-011 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 28 | T-028 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-029 | T-011 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 3 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 5 total:** ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 5 — Library & CRUD Polish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+|-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 29 | T-029 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-001 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 30 | T-030 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-002 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 31 | T-031 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-003 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 32 | T-032 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-004 | T-001 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-005 | T-001 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 34 | T-034 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-006 | T-001 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 35 | T-035 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-007 | T-001 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 36 | T-036 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-008 | T-001 | - OSCend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Taught `face_display.py` to surface the live EMSD sample layer from `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json`, so the head monitor can show which source and activity mode the room-sampling layer is currently holding or triggering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visitests/test_first_boot.py:444:        identity = bootstrap_identity(identity_path=path)\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5358:| 21 | T-021 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-022 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5474:  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5513:| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Z_1776393558.log:11:- `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Z_1776393558.log:41:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T02:39:22.519Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"user\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\